Author: djdarcy
Title: Improved exportMarkdown() & getName() to better preserve user input
Body:
The changes to `scripts/export.js` below add better support to:
* maintain proper carriage returns in the markdown output
* retain indentation by converting appropriate whitespace (spaces, tabs, etc) to ` ` and then calling ExportMD

There is also some stub code to improve the readability of the exported filenames, but this will likely also require changes to some of the Rust code.

Author: asheroto
Title: Update Issue template to avoid non-package Issues
Body:
I noticed that many people are creating an issue for things that have nothing to do with this package.

To help prevent against non-package issues, I have added some additional information at the top, as well as added a checkbox requiring people to check that the issue does not occur on ChatGPT and only in this app. üòä

Author: TungusSs
Title: Added Russian translation, updated README and improved project structure
Body:
Greetings, this is my first PR, please be patient if I did something wrong üòÑ.
I added Russian translation of README and Russian flag icon in the main README to indicate availability of translated version (README-ru.md). This is done to improve accessibility for Russian-speaking users. Also I made a `docs` folder, where all the README translations will be kept and moved README-ZN_CN.md in that folder. If you want, you can make it for other documents (not only README) in the future.
Please forgive me for misprints or translation errors, if I missed something, please point out my mistakes, I will be grateful to you and I will correct them, also you can commit in my PR too.

Author: mrdulin
Title: fix: node version campatible issue
Body:
[issue](https://github.com/lencx/ChatGPT/issues/463)

English: If the user has incompatible Nodejs version, `pnpm install` will throw an error and prevent installing packages. 
Chinese: ÂºÄÂêØengine-strictÔºånodejsÁâàÊú¨‰∏éenginesÂ≠óÊÆµÊåáÂÆöÁöÑÁâàÊú¨‰∏çÂÖºÂÆπÔºåÂàôÊä•ÈîôÂπ∂ÈòªÊ≠¢Áî®Êà∑ÂÆâË£Öpackage

For example:

```bash
$ sudo n node/15.14.0
   installed : v15.14.0 (with npm 7.7.6)

$ pnpm install 
‚ÄâERR_PNPM_UNSUPPORTED_ENGINE‚Äâ Unsupported environment (bad pnpm and/or Node.js version)

Your Node version is incompatible with "/Users/dulin/workspace/github.com/mrdulin/ChatGPT".

Expected version: ^14.18.0 || ^16.0.0
Got: v15.14.0

This is happening because the package's manifest has an engines.node field specified.
To fix this issue, install the required Node version.
```

Body:
Hello,

This PR fixes the cask name in the `brewfile` section. I noticed that this had been causing some confusion for users, so I hope this helps to clear things up.

I also wanted to express my gratitude to you as the maintainer for all of your hard work on this project. Your efforts are greatly appreciated and make a big difference for everyone who uses ChatGPT.

Thank you again for all that you do, and I hope you find this PR to be useful.
